social_posts.post_text:
Some of us are missing teeth because they never formed or erupted like they should have.  Unfortunately, the upper lateral teeth are some of the most common missing teeth and they affect our smile. 
🦁
Luckily, sometimes the space is filled naturally by all your other teeth coming together or using braces we can bring your teeth together.  But that still places a canine or pointy fang tooth where a rectangle shaped tooth should be. 
🦊
My patient came in for a routine check up and wanted to discuss the cosmetics of his smile.  He didn’t like the spaces that the canine tooth created on both sides. 
🐶
Without any anesthesia, I isolated his canine teeth and added some resin with custom staining. Within a few minutes, he had the smile he always wanted! 
🐹
If there is something that just bothers you about your smile or ‘it’s always the first thing you notice in pictures’ ask your dentist about your options to improve your smile.  They may be more simple than you think!!

social_posts.post_text:
Decades ago, two root canals were done in two front teeth. They had both discolored over the years, but my patient was tolerating the deterioration of his smile due his anxiety.  Then one of them cracked straight off at the gumline! 
😩
He would have preferred to avoid getting dental work done because of his painful experience with the root canals decades ago but now he had no choice.
🥺
This was the first time he had visited my office.  I showed him his X-rays and the two abcesses on either tooth. I explained why they had darkened. I explained why he would first need to retreat the root canals. My team helped him get an appointment with the specialist right away and he was back by the afternoon with the root canals retreated and the teeth ready to restore. 
🙂
Financially he would have to wait to restore one of the darkened teeth but the broken one he needed fixed asap. We scanned his smile, removed the broken and cracked tooth structure, placed a fiber post through the tooth and rebuilt it with resin.  Then I prepared his tooth for a full porcelain crown and made the crown while my patient sipped some coffee. 
🤭☕️
The shading of the tooth was tricky because on one side he has a tooth with an old, discolored resin filling and on the other he has a dark, discolored tooth that also needs to be crowned soon. 
🤩🦷
In a couple hours, he had the dentistry done that he had postponed for years. Had he come in before the tooth cracked, the tooth would have had a better long term prognosis. #dentist #dentalhygienist #orlandodentist #dentista #predental #dentalstudent #samedaycrowns

A missing tooth is a cosmetic and functional issue.  You can choose to deal with it later - but once a tooth is missing it is like taking a book out of a packed bookshelf.  Your other teeth begin to shift and move. 
🌺
You can hold your teeth in place with wearing retainers at night.  And when you are ready, find out about a single implant to replace the tooth. 
🌸

Several months ago, we diagnosed tooth #4 as non restorable.  In other words, it needed to come out. I removed the tooth and placed a bone matrix to help preserve the ridge. 
🌸 
This morning, after getting my patient numb and comfortable, I placed a Straumann titanium implant.  The root mimics a real tooth root and is perfectly placed to hold a porcelain crown once it had healed. #we were fine with the procedure in less than 30 minutes. 
🌸
Let me know why you are hesitating to have an implant placed! #dentalimplants #dentalimplantsorlando #orlandoimplants #straumann #orlandodentist #dentistrymyworld #predental #dentalstudent #hunterscreek

You want to fill the space where your molar used to be BUT you don’t want your other teeth to be touched or damaged? It’s as easy as 3,2,1! 
🥉
We will place the implant and let the area heal for a few months. The implant begins to adapt to your body similar to the roots of your other teeth. 
🥈
We will scan the implant with a camera to get its exact position in your mouth compared to your other teeth and begin making the crown in a lab. 
🥇
 The final step is to place the porcelain crown on your implant and cover the opening with a resin filling! #alldone #straumann #dentalimplants #orlandoflorida #orlandodentalimplants #orlandodentista #dentistlife #hunterscreekflorida

Why Choose Veneers? 
Veneers offer an array of benefits that make them a popular choice for smile makeovers. They provide a conservative yet dramatic solution to numerous dental concerns. Here are a few reasons why veneers might be the perfect choice for you:
1️⃣ Instant Transformation: In just a few visits to our dental office, you can achieve a complete smile makeover with veneers. It's a quick and efficient way to enhance your smile without invasive procedures.
2️⃣ Natural Aesthetics: Veneers are designed to mimic the translucency and texture of natural teeth, ensuring a seamless blend with your existing smile. No one will be able to tell the difference!
3️⃣ Stain Resistance: Unlike natural teeth, veneers are highly resistant to staining caused by coffee, tea, or tobacco. You can enjoy a bright, radiant smile for years to come.
4️⃣ Durability: With proper care and maintenance, veneers can last for a decade or more. They offer a long-lasting solution to transform your smile and boost your self-confidence.
#veneers #orlandodentist #orlandoflorida #predental #dentistry #dentist #smile

📷✨ As a dentist, I can't contain my excitement about the transformative power of Invisalign or clear aligner therapy for correcting malocclusion! 🚀💯

🦷😁 Today, I want to share an incredible success story from my patient who embarked on an Invisalign journey to overcome their Class III malocclusion. Witnessing their smile transformation has truly been a joy and a testament to the remarkable capabilities of this cutting-edge orthodontic treatment. 🌟🤩

🔬📚 By gradually and discreetly shifting the teeth, Invisalign helps patients achieve optimal dental alignment and a newfound confidence. 🙌💫

🌈 One of the most remarkable aspects of Invisalign is its virtually invisible appearance. These clear aligners seamlessly blend with the patient's teeth, ensuring a more aesthetically pleasing and comfortable orthodontic experience. 🤫💎

⏰💪 Invisalign also offers unparalleled convenience. Patients can remove the aligners for eating, allowing them to savor their favorite foods without worry or restrictions. Maintaining excellent oral hygiene is equally effortless, as the aligners can be easily taken out for brushing and flossing. 🍽🧼

💼💻 From boardroom meetings to special occasions, Invisalign adapts flawlessly to a patient's lifestyle. It's the ideal solution for individuals leading busy lives who desire a beautiful smile without sacrificing their daily routine. 🎉📸

🙏🌟 If you or someone you know is struggling with Class III malocclusion or any other dental misalignment, I wholeheartedly recommend considering Invisalign as a transformative orthodontic treatment. Schedule a consultation with your dentist to explore how Invisalign can bring a smile transformation to your life. 😊✨

Can you do anything about my dark tooth? Often times traumatic injury to front teeth can cause them to darken over time as the nerve becomes necrotic or dies.  This same darkening can sometimes be seen on previously root canaled teeth. 
We can attempt to lighten the tooth with internal whitening but most of the time we are ‘covering’ the stain with porcelain.  Regardless of cosmetics, the crowning of the tooth with porcelain is usually necessary on a ‘non vital’ (not alive) tooth to keep it strong and prevent chipping as the tooth becomes more brittle with time.  #rootcanal #rootcanaltreatment #dentistry #orlando #kissimmee #orlandodentist

I actually have nightmares of getting injured and breaking my front teeth. In my dreams, my other injuries are meaningless and the focus of the dream turns into a search for a dentist. 
My patient is a lovely lady in her 60s and a fall resulted in breaking her two front teeth.  Like me, she was not concerned of the bruised lips and other facial injuries. “What can be done about my front teeth?,” she kept asking! 
We quickly made her a clear retainer and added resin to look like teeth for the front.  The remaining broken tooth roots were extracted and implants placed.  A few months later, we scanned the implants and made two beautiful front teeth and even replaced an old resin veneer with a new porcelain one. 
Her smile was as beautiful as ever! She took the words right out of my mouth when she said, “Losing my front teeth was my worse nightmare, but this was so much easier than I thought!”. #frontteeth #alliwantforchristmas #implants #dentalimplants #nightmare #orlando #orlandodentist #kissimmee #predental #dentistryworld
